To get the source code either:

  $ git clone https://ashgti@github.com/ashgti/VEE.git

or

  Download https://github.com/ashgti/VEE/zipball/master 


Prerequisites:

  Command Line Simulations:
    CMake 2.8
    Python 2.6 or Python 2.7
    C and C++ Compiler

  Configuration GUI:
    CMake 2.8
    Python 2.6 or Python 2.7
    Qt GUI Framework
    PySide - The Python interfaces to the Qt GUI
    C and C++ Compiler

  Optional Requirements:
    git - Source Code tracking
    Matplotlib - for graphing purposes

This has been tested and developed with Python 2.6, Python 2.7, gcc-4.2,
g++-4.2, gcc-4.5, g++-4.5, Qt 4.7.x, PySide 1.0.x, CMake 2.6, CMake 2.8.

This was tested on Ubuntu Linux 10.04, Ubuntu Linux 10.10, Ubuntu Linux 11.10,
Mac OS X 10.7.

It should work with any operating system that supports the above version of
Python, CMake and Qt.


OS X Install Instructions

Using homebrew:
  $ brew install cmake pyside git
  
  This will install all of the dependencies using brew's package management system.

Without homebrew:
  1. Install XCode
  2. Install CMake, see http://cmake.org/cmake/resources/software.html or http://www.cmake.org/files/v2.8/cmake-2.8.6-Darwin64-universal.dmg
  3. Install Qt and PySide, see http://developer.qt.nokia.com/wiki/PySide_Binaries_MacOSX
    3.a. Install Qt 4.7.4, see http://qt.nokia.com/downloads/qt-for-open-source-cpp-development-on-mac-os-x or http://get.qt.nokia.com/qt/source/qt-mac-opensource-4.7.4.dmg
    3.b. Install PySide, see http://developer.qt.nokia.com/wiki/PySide_Binaries_MacOSX
         Depending on the system default version of python, you will need to install:
           Python2.7 http://pyside.markus-ullmann.de/pyside-1.0.9-qt47-py27apple.pkg
         Or
           Python2.6 http://pyside.markus-ullmann.de/pyside-1.0.9-qt47-py26apple.pkg

         To determine the default version of python, execute:
           $ python --version
           > Python 2.7.1
         The default for OS X 10.6 Snow Leopard is python2.6, the default for OS X 10.7 Lion is python2.7.
  4. Install Matplotlib, see http://matplotlib.sourceforge.net/users/installing.html
    $ easy_install matplotlib
